article.headline: Arkansas St. 72, Louisiana-Monroe 64
article.story: JONESBORO, Ark. -- Ed Townsel and Adam Sterrenberg scored 18 points each to lead Arkansas State to a 72-64 victory against Louisiana-Monroe on Thursday night. Townsel made five 3-pointers, Sterrenberg four. Rakeem Dickerson added 12 points and Marcus Hooten 10 for the Red Wolves (10-14, 4-6 Sun Belt). Brandon Peterson had 10 rebounds. Marcelis Hansberry scored 15 points and Fabio Ribeiro 13 for the Warhawks (2-21, 1-9), who have lost 10 straight at Arkansas State and have not won there since the 1984-85 season. Townsel had seven assists.
